docs.abstract: Tired “tough on crime” rhetoric is not the solution to crime in 2022.
docs.snippet: Tired “tough on crime” rhetoric is not the solution to crime in 2022.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mayor Eric Adams of New York City understands the assignment: to keep the nation’s largest city safe amid an alarming rise in violent crime. At least 40 of the people shot so far this year in New York were children and teenagers, or one in every 10 shooting victims. One of those children, Kade Lewin, 12, was shot and killed while sitting with relatives in a parked car in Brooklyn.

headline.main: Mayor Eric Adams Is Stuck on Ideas From 1994 for Crime in 2022
headline.print_headline: On Crime, Adams Is Stuck in 1994

docs.abstract: These two canonical dance artists, both now 70, share a willingness to take on weighty issues.
docs.snippet: These two canonical dance artists, both now 70, share a willingness to take on weighty issues.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eiko Otake and Bill T. Jones are two celebrated dance artists with different styles, temperaments and cultural backgrounds. What they have in common is their willingness — hunger, really — to take on weighty issues. Otake has been illuminating the environmental damage caused by nuclear accidents. Jones is intimately connected to the struggle against racism.

headline.main: Bill T. Jones and Eiko Otake: Opposites Guided by ‘Too-Much-Ness’

docs.abstract: In 1992, Héctor Tobar was a young reporter at The Los Angeles Times when the city erupted in violence. What really happened — and what didn’t?
docs.snippet: In 1992, Héctor Tobar was a young reporter at The Los Angeles Times when the city erupted in violence. What really happened — and what didn’t?
docs.lead_paragraph: In the spring of 1991, I was in the Los Angeles Times newsroom when word came that a local Black motorist named Rodney King had been nearly beaten to death by the police. Despite the fact that our staff had been writing about sensational cases of police brutality for years, the crisis set off by the videotape of King’s being assaulted seemed to catch us by surprise.

headline.main: The L.A. Riots Were 30 Years Ago. I’m Still Trying to Understand Them.

docs.abstract: The Brooklyn shooting and other headline-making violence are part of a broader trend.
docs.snippet: The Brooklyn shooting and other headline-making violence are part of a broader trend.
docs.lead_paragraph: A gunman opened fire in a Brooklyn subway, wounding 10 people on Tuesday and injuring others. A mall shooting in South Carolina yesterday wounded 10. A gang shootout this month in Sacramento killed six and wounded 12 more. New Orleans reported its bloodiest weekend in 10 years. Road rage shootings appear to be up in some states.
